title: Independent Candidate Munir Hussain wins PK-36 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Munir Hussain has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-36, Manshera-I by securing 35,074 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PMLN) candidate Syed Junaid Ali Qasim who bagged 30,414 votes.
